      "content": "the logs aren't really \"redundant\" in a technical sense—they're just a lot of text data that's slowing down the query speeds for the new season. the policy says anything older than 24 months is non-essential for the core database function. i'm pretty sure it's safe to just let the script wipe the preference notes and historical interaction logs. it's just a standard optimization to keep the luxury service response times fast. why do you think we shouldn't just run it?",
